title: Philippines Unemployment Rate
description: Unemployment Rate in Philippines decreased to 5 percent in September from 5.30 percent in August of 2022. Unemployment Rate in Philippines averaged 8.47 percent from 1986 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 17.60 percent in June of 2020 and a record low of 4.59 percent in December of 2019. In the Philippines, the unemployment rate measures the number of people actively looking for a job as a percentage of the labour force. This page provides - Philippines Unemployment Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Philippine Statistics Authority
